Component Name: Bench press double arm with two DB
Component Description:
Sit down on a utility bench with two dumbbells resting on the lower thighs. Kick weights to shoulder and lie back. Position the dumbbells to the sides of the chest with bent arms under each dumbbell.

Press the dumbbells up with the elbows to the sides until the arms are extended. Lower weights to the sides of the upper chest until a slight stretch is felt in the chest or shoulder. Repeat.

The dumbbells should follow a slight arch pattern, above the upper arm between the elbow and chest at the bottom, traveling inward over each shoulder at the top.
